        <br><br><h3> School Shutdown Lunch Availability </h3>
        <h2> Effective April 1, 2020, anyone aged 18 and under will be able to
          eat for free during the shutdown. </h2>
        <h2> We will be offering breakfast and lunch on Good Friday and Easter
          Monday. </h2>
        <p> <a href="files/announcements/lunch_pickup.pdf" target="_blank">Revised
            Breakfast and Lunch Pickup Procedure </a></p>
        <p> Gettysburg School will be offering "grab and go" breakfast and lunch
          during the school shutdown.</p>
        <p> The meals are to be picked up in the front entryway area. </p>
        <p> The program will start Monday, March 16th</p>
        <p> Breakfast will be available from 8:00am to 9:00am </p>
        <p> Lunch will be available from 11:30am to 12:30pm. You may also pick
          up breakfast for the next day at this time if you would like.</p>
        <p> Please contact the school by 5:00pm the day before you want to eat
          via the following methods: </p>
        <p>You may reach Lexy Gimbel by email at:  <a href="mailto:lexy.gimbel@k12.sd.us">lexy.gimbel@k12.sd.us</a></p>
        <p> You may call or text Barb Everson at:  <a href="tel:605-769-1282">605 769 1282</a>
        </p>
